OL,3,C'My mother lay on the cold road dying'
OL,4,CSon's anger as driver is jailed for
OL,5,Ccrash
OL,7,F"My father has profound mental health
OL,8,Fdifficulties, and my mum was able to
OL,9,Fprotect him from the outside world and
OL,10,Fallow him to live the life that they
OL,11,Fboth wanted.
OL,13,F"Since her death, Dad has had to learn
OL,14,Fto cook, clean, pay bills and deal
OL,15,Fwith all the household expenditures
OL,16,Fand everything else. Family of course
OL,17,Fhelp where we can but we are no
OL,18,Fsubstitute for his loving wife. He is
OL,19,Fa shadow of the man he used to be
OL,20,Fbefore this dreadful incident.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
